Get the values from model weights

get_weights.Rd

Returns weighting variable of a model.

get_weights(x, ...)

Arguments

x

A fitted model.
...

Currently not used.

Value

The weighting variable, or NULL if no weights were specified.

Examples

data(mtcars)
mtcars$weight <- rnorm(nrow(mtcars), 1, .3)
m <- lm(mpg ~ wt + cyl + vs, data = mtcars, weights = weight)
get_weights(m)
#>  [1] 0.8656324 1.3508724 1.3412122 0.9056298 1.0269960 1.0697827 0.8777610
#>  [8] 0.9574806 1.0059007 1.3308397 1.0344228 1.2419049 1.5128011 0.8437868
#> [15] 1.2181576 0.8248433 0.4259231 0.5834718 0.9999351 1.2523928 1.0423013
#> [22] 1.1684668 1.6009714 0.5192650 1.5075580 1.2396518 1.1567115 0.9546780
#> [29] 1.1374583 1.4581880 1.0750441 1.4603094
